messages.text: After Will listens to Angie‚Äôs story about Kyle and the Source, he texts her urgently.
You need to go tell your father.
I can‚Äôt. They‚Äôll kill him instantly.
They‚Äôll kill all of us.
Do you really think they‚Äôre as powerful as they say they are?
That they actually have secret service agents in their back pocket?
I don‚Äôt have any reason to doubt them.
Then you need to threaten them back.
With what?
They‚Äôre powerful enough to keep influencing the government ‚Äî even if I expose them.
So, I can‚Äôt exactly threaten them with taking the ‚Äúsecret‚Äù out of their society.
They‚Äôre invincible, and they know it.
Then we need to get to someone who‚Äôs not invincible.
We need to get to Kyle.
I‚Äôve tried.
He doesn‚Äôt care.
I can‚Äôt believe I thought he loved me.
I feel so stupid.
Angie, he sounds like a sociopath. He made himself into the person he thought you‚Äôd trust.
He tricked you into caring about him.
NONE of this is your fault.
Thanks Will. Hearing that helps.
Well, it‚Äôs the truth.
And it also sounds like this society has put a lot of time and energy into Kyle.
They‚Äôre protecting this ‚Äúplan‚Äù that they have for him above all else, right?
Right.
That means he‚Äôs valuable to them.
And it also means he‚Äôs their weak point.
I guess‚Ä¶
He‚Äôs only one person, Ang. He‚Äôs not invincible.
A secret society with an unknown number of anonymous members might be powerful.
But one person?
One person can crack if you find the right pressure point.
So ‚Äî what‚Äôs Kyle‚Äôs weakness?
I don‚Äôt know. Up until now, he didn‚Äôt seem to have any flaws.
He always did and said the right thing.
And that didn‚Äôt bore you to death?
üòè It was starting to.
All right, we‚Äôll get back to listing your boyfriend requirements once I know you‚Äôre safe.
You said that every member knows a secret about every other member that will completely destroy their reputation, right?
Do you know Kyle‚Äôs secret?
No. I didn‚Äôt get far enough into the process to learn everyone‚Äôs secrets.
And they won‚Äôt trust me with them now.
I told them I wouldn‚Äôt join their evil, political-bullshit cult.
That‚Äôs my girl.
The Source has been texting you, right?
Yes.
So, it stands to reason that they communicate with Kyle the same way?
Yeah, but I don‚Äôt have their number. It always comes up as UNKNOWN.
We don‚Äôt need their number.
But I do need Kyle‚Äôs.
Why?
Because I‚Äôm going to hack into his phone and see what they‚Äôve been talking about.
If we‚Äôre lucky, I‚Äôll be able to dig up the secret Kyle wants to keep buried.
If we‚Äôre really lucky, it‚Äôll be good enough to give you some leverage on him.
You‚Äôre a genius.
I won‚Äôt let them hurt you, Angie.
I don‚Äôt care what it takes.
Even if I have to change my name so we can go into hiding together.
I won‚Äôt let them get to you.
I know.
Hurry.
An hour later, Angie is pacing her bedroom. Her gaze keeps darting over to her locked door.
I‚Äôve found something.
Something big.
Thank God.
What is it?
Pictures of a car accident from a year ago.
A hit and run.
There‚Äôs a body underneath the car.
Send me the pictures.
Will sends the pictures. Angie‚Äôs stomach turns.
She has to force herself not to vomit.
Is that Kyle‚Äôs car?
Definitely.
There are other pictures I didn‚Äôt send.
Pictures of the body being cremated.
And screenshots of texts from the Source telling Kyle they‚Äôve taken care of his ‚Äúproblem.‚Äù
They also said they‚Äôll be holding the photos as collateral.
What kind of collateral?
I don‚Äôt know.
Maybe your boy gave off the impression that he didn‚Äôt want to stay loyal to the society.
Or maybe they wanted extra insurance to make sure he‚Äôd follow their instructions.
Don‚Äôt call him ‚Äúmy boy.‚Äù
He‚Äôs nothing to me.
It‚Äôs okay to feel hurt, you know.
He did betray you.
And you care about him.
Not anymore.
Angie, are you sure you don‚Äôt want to play along for a few more days?
Give yourself more time to make sure this is what you really want to do?
I mean, you are talking about going up against the people who run our entire government, here.
No. Send me everything, including Kyle‚Äôs text chain with the Source.
This ends tonight.
